$ Oracle fast recovery area: disk quota
@ disk quota

The value of the *disk quota* is set with the → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters#db_recovery_file_dest_size[`db_recovery_file_dest_size` init parameter].
It is used to limit the size of the → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/recovery/fast-recovery-area area.

When the disk quota is reached, Oracle automatically deletes files that are no longer needed.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/recovery/fast-recovery-area
